00:13:46.190 --> 00:13:47.730 align:middle line:90%
forever.

00:13:47.730 --> 00:13:51.570 align:middle line:10%
>> We have two immune
systems, interestingly enough.

00:13:51.570 --> 00:13:53.160 align:middle line:10%
One is called the cell-mediated.

00:13:53.160 --> 00:13:55.600 align:middle line:10%
It's sometimes called
the innate immune system.

00:13:55.600 --> 00:13:58.780 align:middle line:84%
And the other is called
the humoral immune system.

00:13:58.780 --> 00:14:01.260 align:middle line:84%
And so the way it
works, if you take

00:14:01.260 --> 00:14:04.080 align:middle line:84%
an example of a disease
like chicken pox,

00:14:04.080 --> 00:14:06.720 align:middle line:84%
so if you encounter a
virus that you've never

00:14:06.720 --> 00:14:10.170 align:middle line:84%
been exposed to before,
it infects your cells.

00:14:10.170 --> 00:14:12.570 align:middle line:84%
So you have thousands,
or maybe even millions,

00:14:12.570 --> 00:14:14.580 align:middle line:90%
of cells that are infected.

00:14:14.580 --> 00:14:17.790 align:middle line:84%
And your body mounts
a white blood cell

00:14:17.790 --> 00:14:21.930 align:middle line:84%
cell-mediated response
to digest and eliminate

00:14:21.930 --> 00:14:24.485 align:middle line:90%
those infected cells.

00:14:24.485 --> 00:14:28.890 align:middle line:84%
Now, the important thing about
that is that creates symptoms,

00:14:28.890 --> 00:14:34.050 align:middle line:84%
fever, rash, mucus, all those
things that we call being sick.

00:14:34.050 --> 00:14:38.640 align:middle line:84%
The important point about that
is what we call being sick

00:14:38.640 --> 00:14:41.140 align:middle line:90%
is the cell-mediated response.

00:14:41.140 --> 00:14:43.740 align:middle line:84%
It's not from the
chicken pox virus.

00:14:43.740 --> 00:14:47.250 align:middle line:84%
The chicken pox virus is
the stimulation for you

00:14:47.250 --> 00:14:48.930 align:middle line:90%
to mount a response.

00:14:48.930 --> 00:14:49.990 align:middle line:90%
Now, how do I know that?

00:14:49.990 --> 00:14:52.200 align:middle line:84%
Because you could give
somebody with chicken pox

00:14:52.200 --> 00:14:54.540 align:middle line:84%
prednisone, and
so that stops them

00:14:54.540 --> 00:14:57.090 align:middle line:84%
from mounting a
cell-mediated response,

00:14:57.090 --> 00:15:00.090 align:middle line:90%
and they will not be "sick".

00:15:00.090 --> 00:15:04.590 align:middle line:84%
They might die from chicken
pox, but they won't be sick.

00:15:04.590 --> 00:15:07.670 align:middle line:84%
And, on the other
hand, you can stimulate

00:15:07.670 --> 00:15:10.800 align:middle line:84%
a cell-mediated
response with chemicals,

00:15:10.800 --> 00:15:14.310 align:middle line:84%
and no virus or infecting
agent is necessary,

00:15:14.310 --> 00:15:16.750 align:middle line:90%
and the person will be sick.

00:15:16.750 --> 00:15:21.940 align:middle line:84%
So that's how our innate
immune system works.

00:15:21.940 --> 00:15:24.900 align:middle line:84%
But you can notice
it by just observing

00:15:24.900 --> 00:15:26.820 align:middle line:90%
what happens to a person.

00:15:26.820 --> 00:15:30.930 align:middle line:84%
That which you can see, that's
the cell-mediated innate immune

00:15:30.930 --> 00:15:32.580 align:middle line:90%
system working.

00:15:32.580 --> 00:15:35.130 align:middle line:84%
Then, once that
happens, and you clear

00:15:35.130 --> 00:15:38.190 align:middle line:84%
the virus and the
dead cells, and you're

00:15:38.190 --> 00:15:39.940 align:middle line:90%
better than you were before.

00:15:39.940 --> 00:15:42.630 align:middle line:84%
So you've actually
improved your health now

00:15:42.630 --> 00:15:44.250 align:middle line:90%
that you're done with this.

00:15:44.250 --> 00:15:46.120 align:middle line:90%
You've cleansed your body.

00:15:46.120 --> 00:15:49.210 align:middle line:84%
Then, you make antibodies so
you remember what happened,

00:15:49.210 --> 00:15:51.840 align:middle line:84%
so if you encountered
chicken pox again,

00:15:51.840 --> 00:15:55.920 align:middle line:84%
you tag it and eliminate
it before it has a chance

00:15:55.920 --> 00:15:59.400 align:middle line:84%
to infect your cells, so
you'll never get sick again

00:15:59.400 --> 00:16:01.590 align:middle line:90%
from that virus.

00:16:01.590 --> 00:16:05.700 align:middle line:84%
And those two working
together for eons

00:16:05.700 --> 00:16:08.160 align:middle line:90%
is how the immune system works.

